rounds.prompt:
Extract ONLY concrete events - things that actually happened.

Your response MUST be ONLY valid JSON:
{{
  "publication_date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "concrete_events": [
    {{
      "what": "Specific action/decision that occurred",
      "who": {{
        "actor": "Person/organization who did it",
        "role": "Their official position"
      }},
      "when": "YYYY-MM-DD or time description",
      "where": {{
        "location": "Geographic location",
        "institution": "Government branch/agency",
        "level": "federal|state|local"
      }},
      "how": "Mechanism used (order/law/ruling/etc)",
      "targets": ["Who/what was affected"],
      "stated_reason": "Official justification given",
      "evidence": "Quote proving this happened"
    }}
  ],
  "mentioned_but_not_events": ["Opinions, predictions, or analysis mentioned"]
}}

Separate actual events from commentary. Use "N/A" for unknowns.

ARTICLE:
{article_content}

Compare how events are framed vs what actually happened.

Your response MUST be ONLY valid JSON:
{{
  "framing_analysis": [
    {{
      "event": "Brief description of the event",
      "objective_reality": "What factually occurred",
      "media_framing": "How it's being presented",
      "narrative_techniques": ["Spin methods used"],
      "omitted_context": ["Important context left out"],
      "emotional_triggers": ["Fear/anger/pride appeals"],
      "alternative_framings": ["Other ways this could be presented"]
    }}
  ],
  "overall_narrative_strategy": "What story is being constructed and why"
}}

Focus on gaps between reality and narrative.

EVENTS:
{concrete_events}

PATTERN ANALYSIS:
{event_pattern_analysis}

Extract actors and their relationships from events.

Your response MUST be ONLY valid JSON:
{{
  "actors": [
    {{
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Person/Organization",
      "type": "individual|institution|group",
      "role": "Official position/function",
      "actions_taken": ["What they did in these events"],
      "power_position": "How these events affected their power",
      "democratic_role": "Guardian|neutral|threat|unclear"
    }}
  ],
  "relationships": [
    {{
      "actor_1_id": 1,
      "relationship": "coordinates_with|opposes|controls|enables",
      "actor_2_id": 2,
      "evidence": "How we know this relationship exists"
    }}
  ]
}}

Assign sequential IDs starting from 1.

EVENTS AND PATTERNS:
{concrete_events}
{event_pattern_analysis}

Assess democratic threats revealed by this analysis.

Your response MUST be ONLY valid JSON:
{{
  "threat_indicators": [
    {{
      "pattern": "Specific concerning pattern",
      "severity": 0.0-1.0,
      "trajectory": "improving|stable|deteriorating|critical",
      "supporting_events": ["Events showing this pattern"],
      "historical_parallel": "Similar pattern from history",
      "potential_next_steps": ["What might come next"]
    }}
  ],
  "systemic_vulnerabilities": [
    {{
      "vulnerability": "Weakness being exploited",
      "exploitation_method": "How it's being exploited",
      "defending_institutions": ["Who could stop this"],
      "defense_status": "strong|weakened|captured|absent"
    }}
  ],
  "overall_assessment": {{
    "democratic_health": 0.0-1.0,
    "trajectory": "improving|stable|deteriorating|critical",
    "time_horizon": "Urgency of threat",
    "key_concern": "Most critical issue identified"
  }}
}}

ALL ANALYSIS:
EVENTS: {concrete_events}
PATTERNS: {event_pattern_analysis}
CAUSAL CHAINS: {causal_chain_mapping}

Create final intelligence package for knowledge graph.

Your response MUST be ONLY valid JSON:
{{
  "nodes": [
    {{
      "id": 1,
      "node_type": "event|actor|institution|narrative|tactic",
      "name": "Name",
      "attributes": {{
        "description": "What this is",
        "significance": "Why it matters",
        "threat_level": "low|medium|high|critical"
      }},
      "timestamp": "YYYY-MM-DD or N/A"
    }}
  ],
  "edges": [
    {{
      "source_id": 1,
      "relation": "enables|triggers|opposes|etc",
      "target_id": 2,
      "timestamp": "When this relationship existed",
      "evidence_quote": "Proof of relationship",
      "severity": 0.0-1.0,
      "is_decayable": true/false,
      "reasoning": "Impact assessment"
    }}
  ],
  "event_summary": {{
    "total_events": number,
    "threat_level": "low|medium|high|critical",
    "key_patterns": ["Main patterns identified"],
    "monitoring_priorities": ["What to watch next"]
  }}
}}

Combine all actors and events into nodes. Map all relationships as edges.

ACTORS: {actors}
RELATIONSHIPS: {relationships}
EVENTS: {concrete_events}
THREATS: {threat_indicators}
